HOW TO INSTALL
--------------

Using the 'install' script
--------------------------

To install/upgrade modules in this directory, run

./install

You may specify other prefix than the default (usually /usr) with

./install --prefix=<other-prefix>


Manually
--------

To install selected modules manually, unpack the archives and follow
instructions in INSTALL/README files provided.

In general, C libraries are to be installed using

./configure [--prefix=<prefix>]
make
make test
make install

while Perl modules are installed with the following commands:

perl Makefile.PL [PREFIX=<prefix>] [module-specific options]
make
make test
make install

